    <description>The purpose of this experiment was to obtain radar images, combined with altimetry and radiometry measurements, over the majority of Venus' surface. The radar sensor unit was contained in a single unit of overall dimensions 1.27 x 0.76 x 0.30 m. The radar system used the 3.7 m diameter high-gain antenna for synthetic aperture radar (SAR) observations and radiometry. A smaller, fan-beam antenna was used for the altimetry measurements.</description>
